Output:
The specific objectives of the study were: 
1) to monitor the biochemical properties of four dominant shrub species in the polluted and control areas; 
2) to study the long-term consequences of the contamination; 
3) to provide information that will assist in planning rehabilitation actions; 
4) to explore the feasibility of VIs, along with the machine learning (ML) technique, for detecting stressed shrubs based on the full spectral range.
